        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:52PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near South
Charleston, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Springfield, London, Jefferson, West Jefferson, Mount Sterling, South
Charleston, Choctaw Lake, Harmony, Lisbon, Brighton, Lafayette, South
Vienna, South Solon, Midway, Catawba, Newport, Interstate 70 at US
Route 42, Chenoweth, Lilly Chapel, and State Route 29 at State Route
38.

This includes the following Interstates...
I-70 in Ohio between mile markers 60 and 84.
I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 77 and 87.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
